\ Deque and priority queue regressions.

'check [ [ ] [ "deque/pqueue check failed" error ] ifelse ] def

[ 1 2 3 ] >deque deque? true == check
[ 1 2 3 ] >deque type-of "deque" == check
[ 1 2 3 ] >deque len 3 == check
[ ] >deque empty? true == check
[ 1 "two" ] >deque repr "[1 \"two\"] >deque" == check

[ 1 2 3 ] >deque items [ 1 2 3 ] == check
"abc" >deque items [ "a" "b" "c" ] == check
[ 1 2 ] >deque 0 push-front items [ 0 1 2 ] == check
[ 1 2 ] >deque 3 push-back items [ 1 2 3 ] == check
[ 1 2 ] >deque dup 0 push-front items [ 0 1 2 ] == check
items [ 1 2 ] == check
[ 1 2 ] >deque dup 3 push-back items [ 1 2 3 ] == check
items [ 1 2 ] == check
[ 1 2 3 ] >deque first 1 == check
[ 1 2 3 ] >deque last 3 == check

[ 1 2 3 ] >deque pop-front 1 == check items [ 2 3 ] == check
[ 1 2 3 ] >deque pop-back 3 == check items [ 1 2 ] == check
[ 1 2 3 ] >deque dup pop-front 1 == check items [ 2 3 ] == check
items [ 1 2 3 ] == check
[ 1 2 3 ] >deque pop-front push-front [ 1 2 3 ] >deque == check
[ 1 2 3 ] >deque pop-back push-back [ 1 2 3 ] >deque == check
[ [ ] >deque pop-front ] [ "empty-deque" ] try "empty-deque" == check
[ [ ] >deque pop-back ] [ "empty-deque" ] try "empty-deque" == check
[ 1 2 ] >deque [ 1 2 ] >deque == check

\ Exercise ring-buffer wraparound and growth beyond the initial allocation.
[ 0 1 2 3 ] >deque pop-front drop pop-front drop 4 push-back 5 push-back
items [ 2 3 4 5 ] == check
[ ] >deque 1000 [ dup len push-back ] times
dup len 1000 == check
500 [ pop-front drop ] times
dup first 500 == check
dup last 999 == check
drop

[ [ 10 "low" ] [ 1 "urgent" ] [ 5 "mid" ] ] >pqueue pqueue? true == check
[ [ 10 "low" ] [ 1 "urgent" ] [ 5 "mid" ] ] >pqueue type-of "pqueue" == check
[ [ 10 "low" ] [ 1 "urgent" ] [ 5 "mid" ] ] >pqueue len 3 == check
[ ] >pqueue empty? true == check
[ [ 2 "two" ] [ 1 "one" ] ] >pqueue repr
"[[1 \"one\"] [2 \"two\"]] >pqueue" == check

[ [ 10 "low" ] [ 1 "urgent" ] [ 5 "mid" ] ] >pqueue pq-peek
"urgent" == check 1 == check len 3 == check
[ [ 1.0 "float" ] ] >pqueue pq-peek
"float" == check 1.0 == check pairs [ [ 1.0 "float" ] ] == check
[ [ 10 "low" ] [ 1 "urgent" ] [ 5 "mid" ] ] >pqueue pairs
[ [ 1 "urgent" ] [ 5 "mid" ] [ 10 "low" ] ] == check
[ [ 1 "a" ] [ 1 "b" ] [ 1 "c" ] ] >pqueue pairs
[ [ 1 "a" ] [ 1 "b" ] [ 1 "c" ] ] == check
[ [ 1.0 "a" ] [ 1 "b" ] ] >pqueue dup pairs >pqueue == check
[ [ 9007199254740993 "higher" ] [ 9007199254740992.0 "lower" ] ] >pqueue pq-pop
"lower" == check 9007199254740992.0 == check drop

[ ] >pqueue 2 "two" pq-push 1 "one" pq-push pairs
[ [ 1 "one" ] [ 2 "two" ] ] == check
[ [ 10 "low" ] [ 1 "urgent" ] [ 5 "mid" ] ] >pqueue pq-pop
"urgent" == check 1 == check pairs [ [ 5 "mid" ] [ 10 "low" ] ] == check
[ [ ] >pqueue pq-pop ] [ "empty-pqueue" ] try "empty-pqueue" == check
[ [ ] >pqueue pq-peek ] [ "empty-pqueue" ] try "empty-pqueue" == check

\ Shared push/pop preserve the original priority queue.
[ [ 1 "one" ] [ 2 "two" ] ] >pqueue dup 0 "zero" pq-push swap
pairs [ [ 1 "one" ] [ 2 "two" ] ] == check
pairs [ [ 0 "zero" ] [ 1 "one" ] [ 2 "two" ] ] == check
[ [ 1 "one" ] [ 2 "two" ] ] >pqueue dup pq-pop
"one" == check 1 == check pairs [ [ 2 "two" ] ] == check
pairs [ [ 1 "one" ] [ 2 "two" ] ] == check

\ Exercise heap growth and repeated logarithmic removal.
[ ] >pqueue 1000 [ dup len dup pq-push ] times
dup len 1000 == check
pq-peek 0 == check 0 == check
500 [ pq-pop drop drop ] times
dup len 500 == check
pq-peek 500 == check 500 == check
drop

[ [ 2 "b" ] [ 1 "a" ] ] >pqueue [ [ 1 "a" ] [ 2 "b" ] ] >pqueue == check
[ [ 1 "a" ] ] >pqueue [ [ 1.0 "a" ] ] >pqueue == check
[ [ 1 "a" ] [ 1 "b" ] ] >pqueue [ [ 1 "b" ] [ 1 "a" ] ] >pqueue != check
[ [ [ "bad" "x" ] ] >pqueue ] [ "bad-priority" ] try "bad-priority" == check
